          "activity_type": "patch_acked",
          "subject": "Re: [PATCH] btrfs: test create a bunch of files with name hash collision",
          "message_id": "20260305175643.GB1172981@zen.localdomain",
          "url": "https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260305175643.GB1172981@zen.localdomain/",
          "date": "2026-03-05T17:56:04Z",
          "in_reply_to": null,
          "ack_type": "Reviewed-by",
          "is_ongoing": false,
          "submitted_date": null,
          "patch_version": 1,
          "version_history": [],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch tests the creation of multiple files in Btrfs with name hash collisions by generating a large number of file names that collide due to their hash values. The test is designed to ensure that Btrfs handles these collisions correctly, and it could potentially be extended to other filesystems or to generate more names if needed.",
          "analysis_source": "llm-per-reviewer",
          "review_comments": [
            {
              "author": "Filipe Manana",
              "summary": "reviewer questioned the method used to generate file names in the test, noting that it uses a brute force approach and suggesting an alternative mode to generate more names\n\nReviewer noted that generating the file names for the test takes a long time and suggested including a mode to 'generate more' names, which could be generalized to other filesystems",
              "sentiment": "NEUTRAL",
              "sentiment_signals": [
                "questioning implementation",
                "suggestion for improvement",
                "NEEDS_WORK"
              ],
              "has_inline_review": false,
              "tags_given": [
                "Reviewed-by"
              ],
              "raw_body": "By brute force. There's btrfs-crc.c in btrfs-progs for that, I\nslightly changed it to allow for brute forcing with random lengths\nrather than fixed lengths and with more ascii characters ($, _, -,\netc).\n\n---\n\nThat takes a lot of time to generate, that's why I used a hardcoded list.\nIt took about 4 hours to generate these names, using 12 processes in parallel.\n\nThanks.",
              "reply_to": "Boris Burkov",
              "message_date": "2026-03-05",
              "message_id": "CAL3q7H6cR_utsRReNbZLL6x2KgZvLeSaLL8JDuzayOH=hU4jkw@mail.gmail.com",
              "analysis_source": "llm"
            }
          ]
        },
